{% extends "_layout.twig" %}

{# It's rare you'd ever want to output the homepage title of so the value here doesn't matter much #}
{% set title = "Reference" %}
{# Set the slug to empty to simulate an empty segment in Craft #}
{% set slug = "reference" %}

{% set pageHeaderColor = "bg-primary--dark" %}
{% set pageHeaderImg = ' style="background-image: url(/imgs/placeholders/landscape.jpg)"' %}

{% set external %}
 target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="Link opens in new tab"
{% endset %}

{% block content %}
{% include 'reference/_partials/_quick-nav.twig' %}

<div class="bg-grey--lighter  pad" id="intro">
  <section class="site-container">

    <h2 data-bk-layout class="font-xxl font-thin">{{ title }}</h2>

    <div data-bk-layout="palm:9 hands:8 lap:7" data-bk-links="primary fade" class="rte">
      <p class="font-m">Basekit is a frontend framework designed to speed up the development of <a href="https://fortytwo.studio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FortyTwo Studio</a> web projects while balancing flexibility, optimisation, and consistency with the source graphic design.</p>

      <p>You’ll need <a href="http://gulpjs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gulp</a> to optimise and build project files. Experience using of <a href="http://sass-lang.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sass</a> and <a href="https://twig.sensiolabs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Twig</a> is expected and you’ll need to configure the host and proxy values in the browserSync Gulp task if you want things to be awesome.</p>
    </div>

    {% include "reference/_partials/_status.twig" with { value : 80 } %}

  </section>
</div>


  <div class="bg-white pad">
    <div class="site-container">

      <h3 data-bk-layout="pad:trl" class="font-l">Getting started</h3>

      <div data-bk-layout="lap:8" data-bk-links="primary underline fade exit" class="rte">

        <p>While the frontend templates are built with, Twig to streamline the integration with Craft CMS templates, the core framework does not require Craft CMS to be used.</p>

        <p>You’ll also want a local server of some kind, we currently prefer <a href="https://laravel.com/docs/5.4/valet" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Laravel Valet</a> for small static sites and initial frontend templating, like this.</p>

        <p>Once you've downloaded Basekit, cd in to the directory and run <code>$ npm install</code> to get the required Gulp packages.</p>

        <p>Run <code>$ gulp</code> and it should start watching and compiling the relevant files, at the moment this includes: Sass (to .css), Twig (to .html), HTML (to minified and cleaned .html) and finally Javascript to minified and combined .js. It should also open the default local domain (basekit.dev:3000/demo/) with BrowserSync.</p>

        <p>Now that you've comfirmed that Gulp is running, you're ready to start configuring Sass files (and Twig if you're using that).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>


  <div class="bg-white--tint pad" data-bk-links="primary underline fade exit">
    <div class="site-container">
      <h3 data-bk-layout class="font-l">Basekit Structure</h3>

      <div data-bk-layout="pad:rbl hands:6">
        <dl class="alert alert--neutral alert--simple">
          <dt class="font-m">bower_components</dt>
          <dd>Only used to keep the html5shiv snippet up to date… not often.</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div data-bk-layout="pad:rbl hands:6">
        <dl class="alert alert--neutral alert--simple">
          <dt class="font-m">css</dt>
          <dd>The core of Basekit.</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div data-bk-layout="pad:rbl hands:6">
        <dl class="alert alert--neutral alert--simple">
          <dt class="font-m">demo</dt>
          <dd>Static templates are compile to this directory, plus documentation.</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div data-bk-layout="pad:rbl hands:6">
        <dl class="alert alert--neutral alert--simple">
          <dt class="font-m">imgs</dt>
          <dd>Logos, placeholders, UI images etc.</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div data-bk-layout="pad:rbl hands:6">
        <dl class="alert alert--neutral alert--simple">
          <dt class="font-m">js</dt>
          <dd>Project javascript files, numbered files will be compiled and minified into min/basekit.js in their numerical order.</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div data-bk-layout="pad:rbl hands:6">
        <dl class="alert alert--neutral alert--simple">
          <dt class="font-m">node_modules</dt>
          <dd>Gulp dependencies, make sure this isn't committed to git.</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div data-bk-layout="pad:rbl hands:6">
        <dl class="alert alert--neutral alert--simple">
          <dt class="font-m">templates</dt>
          <dd>Twig project templates, compile to demo.</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
